        "text": ", all of him hairy, like a cloak); the fur cloak, or hair mantle, forming one notion (Gesenius). The appearance of the child's body, covered with an unusual quantity of red hair, was \"a sign of excessive sensual vigor and wildness\" (Keil), \"a foreboding of the animal violence of his character\" (Kalisch), \"the indication of a passionate and precocious nature\" (Murphy). ",
